parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal bumper can cause the brake lights to remain illuminated permanently, even when the brakes are released, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded. The vehicle may also go into "limp mode," limiting engine performance and transmission shifting.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
engine and transmission go into "limp mode
" hill-start assist and traction control no longer work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear view camera can reduce the driver's visibility when reversing, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Rear view camera displays a blank or distorted image

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical wiring harness can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, including the backup camera, trunk release, and exterior lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: AdvancedTrac and Hill Assist System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the AdvancedTrac and Hill Assist system can cause the vehicle to become unstable, increasing the risk of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Heated and Cooled Seat Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heated and cooled seat module can cause electrical system malfunctions, including burnt wiring and overheating.
symptoms: Heated and cooled seats not functioning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch pad can cause the brake lights to remain on, even when the brake pedal is not depressed, leading to a loss of power and acceleration, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake lights remain on even when the brake pedal is not depressed
and the vehicle may suddenly decelerate without warning.
